Ducktail is a new game in the Schafkopf family, for 2 players.

Seventeen tricks are played each hand; certain cards are worth certain points; the object is to capture 61+ points. There are bonuses for capturing 9s (especially the 9 of trumps); there are additional bonuses for winning the last trick with a 9.

A pack of 36 cards is used consisting of A K Q J 10 9 8 7 6 in four suits (hearts, diamonds, clubs and spades).&nbsp;

Half of the pack (18 cards) is trumps. The face cards are promoted to be permanent top trumps (ranked in a specific order, by suit) with all the rest of the cards, in a named trump suit, ranking below them.&nbsp;

North America, the 1920s. There is an old mansion surrounded by disturbing rumours: &ldquo;The owner, a wealthy man, was devoted to ancient and blasphemous cult.&rdquo;, &ldquo;A decade ago, the inhabitants suddenly vanished.&rdquo;, &ldquo;All who entered the mansion disappeared, and the few who returned took their own lives soon after.&rdquo;&hellip; The many strange phenomena that occur here hold a dark fascination attracting experts in mysticism and magic. Then, one day, the mansion is visited by a new group of people: A team of investigators from Miskatonic University. How they will end up only depends on the mysterious girl who will hold their fate in her hands&hellip;

Madness Hour is an asymmetrical cooperative game of exploration, based on the Cthulhu Mythos by the works of H. P. Lovecraft. One of the players takes the role of the mysterious girl, while the others play investigators, searching for ancient artefacts and trying to escape from a dangerous mansion. You won&rsquo;t know whether the girl you will encounter in the mansion is human or something more terrifying. The girl&rsquo;s intentions will depend on her identity, and she will manipulate and change the course of the investigators and the objects they hold. As they investigate, they will have to try and figure out what she is and what she is not.

The mysterious relics that the investigators find in the mansion will drive them into madness and turn them into something else. The investigation within the dark mansion is a mixture of madness and suspicion, leading to unexpected consequences. Will you be able to unravel the true identity of the mysterious girl who controls your destiny and escape from the mansion &ndash; while still being human&hellip;?

&ndash; &ldquo;Emma, there&rsquo;s been a breach in the starboard aft hatch. Something has entered the ship.&rdquo;
&ndash; &ldquo;Can you see what it is?&rdquo;
&ndash; &ldquo;I cannot, sorry. Whatever it is, it is draining the energy in this sector and expanding quickly. Emma, I think the ship is in danger&hellip;&rdquo;

An alien lifeform has broken into the ship and intends to turn it into its lair. Of course, the crew members have no place in the alien&rsquo;s plans, except perhaps as food&hellip; Only one thing can save them: creating a powerful virus that kills the creature, along with all its creations. The chances are slim and the creature get stronger and stronger with time. But they have one thing in their favor: this time, ADELE is on their side.

This Kickstarter-exclusive expansion presents a whole new scenario to use along with ADELE base game. A new set of pieces helps track the progress of the alien player while a new set of objects help the crew members face this new threat.

A mission pack expansion for 1-48TACTIC, set in 1944, during the Ardennes offensive. A small group of German Volksgrenadier fight it off with US Airborne for the control of a fuel dump.
Requires at least 1 starter pack per faction and the basic rulebook, works better with a couple of extra additional figures.

Includes:

     a booklets with all the rules;
     a unique metal figures of a German soldier running with a jerrycan and a 25mm round plastic base;
     three resin fuel dump models (each 80x40mm)
     one jerrycan sticks (6 jerrycans);
     ten numbered fold and cut-out dummy


markers with corresponding tokens;

     three fold and cut-out fuel markers.


Requires items from the base game to play.

A mission pack expansion for 1-48TACTIC, set in 1944, during the Ardennes offensive, based on the real Battle of Lanzerath Ridge which was fought on the very first day of the Battle of the Bulge, near the village of Lanzerath, Belgium, along the key route for the German advance on the northern shoulder of the operation. A small group of US Infantry facing a whole German battalion of Fallschirmj&auml;gers try to hold off overwhelmingly superior forces for as long as possible.

The US forces here plays an outnumbered defender that must delay the German attacker as long as possible.  The German forces are overwhelmingly superior and will eventually prevail, but the limited amount of AT available greatly limit the ability of the German player to exploit his superiority in men and firepower. Moreover the attackers have to move to reach their objective, while the defenders can use most of their Actions to fire on them.

pack includes:
&bull; A 52 pages full color booklet with all the rules;
&bull; A special metal figures of a German Fallschirmj&auml;ger armed with a rifle grenade launcher (25mm round plastic base included);
&bull; A special resin figures of a US soldier firing a .50 M2 machine gun (two models of which are also included);
&bull; Resin models of a small log hut, a camouflaged timber pillbox and a dug-in armored jeep.

Requires items from the base game to play.

Great War Commander Battle Pack Nr1 is the first of what will be many themed scenario packs for use with the Great War Commander series of games.

This first Battle Pack is focused on the western front with actions opposing the German forces to the US, British, French and even Portuguese troops.

This Battle Pack features 12 new scenarios - one of which is an amphibious assault - as well as a thrilling Verdun campaign.
It also includes 2 stunning new maps and 113 new counters with new units (French Foreign Legion), new tanks (mark I), and new weapons (37mm infantry gun).

&mdash;description from the designer

COMPONENTS
Two new maps (maps 23 & 24)
Twelve new Scenarios (see below) 
One Verdun campaign
113 die-cut counters
28 additional counters to correct BEF colorization

Rules for Smoke, Beach terrain and updated Artillery table
The Verdun campaign is played in a series of linked "battles". It portrays the April 1916fights for the Mort Homme and C&ocirc;te 304.
Map 23 depicts a specific location: Hill60 (accurate to actual trench map)

The scenarios in GWC: BP Nr1 include:


    33 "&Eacute;tr&eacute;pilly" French (Zouaves and Chasseurs) vs Germans, 7 September 1914;
    34 "Race to the Bridge" British (Royal Marines) vs Germans, 9 October 1914;
    35 "Garibaldi Legion" French Foreign Legion (Italian volunteers) vs Germans, 26 December 1914;
    36 "Hill 60 Chapter I" British vs Germans, british mining and attack on Hill 60 17 April 1915;
    37 "Hill 60 Chapter II" British vs Germans, german counterattack on Hill 60 18 April 1915;
    38 "Landships" Canadians vs Germans, first appearance of the tanks (Mark I) 15 September 1916;
    39 "Primera Patrulha" Portuguese (CEP) vs Germans, 2 June 1917;
    40 "Operation Hush" British vs Germans, the amphibious assault that never was, August 1917;
    41 "Following the Tanks" Highlanders vs Germans, 20 November 1917;
    42 "Faverolles" French vs Germans, 3 June 1918;
    43 "Guillemont Farm" US vs Germans, 29 September 1918;
    44 "Fast and Frious" US vs Germans,  Sgt York's Medal of Honor, 8 October 1918;


NOTE: GWC:BP Nr1 is not a complete game and requires ownership of both Great War Commander and Great War Commander: BEF to play.

Expand your operations with this 5th player expansion which takes Titan&rsquo;s levels of player interaction even further. The race intensifies with the arrival of an additional competitor as you compete to be the first to complete Objectives, fulfil Planetary Orders, exploit Rigs and reach Titan&rsquo;s treasure filled core&hellip;

Includes everything you need to play with a 5th player!

&mdash;description from the publisher

Les Tr&eacute;sors du Pharaon ("The Pharaoh's Treasures") features the new, highly sought-after Pharaoh tiles to add on the Market board. These extraordinary items stand out for their value, of course, but also for their versatility, as they can be used in sets of either of the 2 depicted goods. However, they also come with Corruption, so think twice before you leap on them&hellip;

This expansion also includes 2 new Characters tiles and 2 new Pirogue tokens.

&mdash;description from the publisher
